A four-year-old boy has been taken to hospital after being hit by a car.It happened on Featherstall Road South in Oldham at about 16:15 BST on Sunday, Greater Manchester Police said.The force said the boy's injuries were not believed to be life-threatening and no arrests had been made.North West Ambulance Service said the boy was taken to Manchester Royal Infirmary by ambulance.
